{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2024-01-05","name":"WILLIAM DE CALTHORPE","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"WILLIAM DE CALTHORPE","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"WILLIAM"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"DE CALTHORPE"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"gender":"Male","lifespan":"1241–1306","fullLifespan":"1241–1306","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"PHOTO","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7763-125177-180947-92/dist.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/173123243","thumbnailUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7763-125177-180947-92/thumb200s.jpg?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","deepZoomUrl":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/deepzoomcloud/dzpatron/v1/TH-7763-125177-180947-92/scale?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","headline":"71597 William Calthorpe Male GFQ3-QPF Birth CHILDREN(3) 1241","@type":"ImageObject"}],"birthDate":"+1241","birthPlace":{"address":"Hales, Norfolk, England","geo":{"latitude":52.51136,"longitude":1.50796,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1306","deathPlace":{"address":"Hales, Norfolk, England","geo":{"latitude":52.51136,"longitude":1.50796,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"«b»Biography«/b»\nWalter the Bishop in his will calls Sir Roger de Hales his brother, and was probably father of William de Calthorp the Bishop's nephew and heir, who was afterwards a knight: King Henry III. in his 40th year granted to him free warren in all his demean lands here, that no one should without his leave and license enter therein, to take or pursue any game under the penalty of 10l.\n\nSir William married Cecilia, daughter of Sir Phillip, and sister and heir to William de Burnham, alias Warren, descended(as it is said) from a cousin-german of Hameline Plantaginet Earl Warren and Surrey, and bore for his arms, checque, or and azure, a fess ermine. Some take them to be the arms of the De Burnhams, alias Warren, a younger branch of the Earl Warren's,  which Sir William Calthorpe took up on his marriage with Cecilia aforesaid; but it is more probable the Calthorps bore them, as dependants on the Earls Warren, their capital lords, under whom they held several lordships; and it appears that Walter the Bishop, and uncle to this William, bore the same; and in the 30th of Henry II. when a fine was levied between Matthew de Gourney, and Rose his wife, and Phillip de Burnham, of the manor of Harpley, before John Bishop of Norwich, and Adam de Glanvil, the King's justices, Phillip's seal was the same with that of Hameline Earl Warren; this Sir William Calthorp, and Sir Ralph de Hemmenhale were founders of Burnham priory in 1241.\n\nSir Walter de Calthorp was his son and heir, by Cecilia, and married Ela, daughter of Sir Hervy Stanhowe, lord of Stanhowe.","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1241","date":"1241","place":"Hales, Norfolk, England"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1241","date":"1241","place":"Calthorpe, Norfolk, England","age":"0","id":"GFQ3-Z4N"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1265","date":"1265","place":"Burnham, Norfolk, England","age":"24","id":"LLH9-SFK"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1267","date":"Abt 1267","place":"Burnham Thorpe,Norfolk,England","age":"26","id":"LZ48-71X"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1269","date":"1269","place":"Seething, Loddon, Norfolk, England","age":"28","id":"G3P1-2ST"},{"name":"Death of Spouse","sources":"0","year":"1269","date":"1269","place":"Selkirk Hall, Sale, Norfolk, England","age":"28","id":"GZXT-GJ3"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1306","date":"1306","place":"Hales, Norfolk, England","age":"65"}],"parent":[{"name":"ROGER DE CALTHORPE","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1220–1241","birthDate":"+1220","deathDate":"+1241","age":21,"@type":"Person","identifier":"GFQ3-Z4N","url":"http